{
  "texts": [
    "Batch normalization (54), which accelerates training and improves convergence, and dropout regularization (55), which helps prevent overfitting, are also used to enhance model training stability.",
    "Risk stratification and personalized intervention: individuals are stratified using clustering (e.g., k-means) and quantile binning to generate targeted dietary guidance.",
    "Outputs guide interventions addressing common deficiencies, including calcium and vitamin D (48).",
    "Validation and performance metrics: model reliability is validated using external datasets and evaluated with metrics such as AUC-ROC and calibration plots (56, 57).",
    "Tools such as Scikit-learn (58) ensure reproducibility and comparability across pipelines."
  ]
}